BY AGNES NWORIE, ABAKALIKI The Ebonyi State Police Command has arraigned an aide to Governor David Umahi of the state, Emmanuel Uzor, for allegedly stealing tubers of cassava. The 38-year-old defendant is Umahi’s Special Assistant on Vegetable Market Development and Maintenance. Uzor was the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor before he was appointed Special Assistant. In a suit marked MAB/53C/2023, Uzor was accused of stealing cassava tubers, valued at N600,000.00, property of a resident of the state, Nnamdi Aniedo. He was said to have committed the act on April 30, 2022 at the Kpiri-kpiri axis of Abakaliki, the Ebonyi State capital. The former chief press secretary was docked before an Abakaliki Magistrate’s Court presided over by Esther Ezeugo on January 25, 2023 on a one-count charge of stealing. Police Prosecutor, Inspector Chinedu Mbam, said the defendant committed an offence punishable under Section 390 of the Criminal Code Cap 33 Volume 1, Laws of Ebonyi State of Nigeria, 2009. The charge reads, “That you Emmanuel Uzor on the 30th day of April 2022 at Kpiri-kpiri, Abakaliki in Abakaliki Magisterial District, did steal tubers of cassava valued at Six Hundred Thousand Naira (N600,000.00), property of one Nnamdi Aniedo and thereby committed an offence contrary to and punishable under Section 390 of the Criminal Code Cap 33 Volume 1, Laws of Ebonyi State of Nigeria, 2009.” Uzor pleaded not guilty to the allegation. Defence counsel, Innocent Nwudenyi, applied for the Special Assistant’s bail and assured the court that he had reliable people to stand as surety for him. Nwudenyi described the charge as a mere allegation to tarnish the image of Uzor, who is a journalist. However, the police prosecutor did not object to the oral bail application. The trail Magistrate, Ezeugo, granted bail to the defendant in the sum of N50,000 and one reliable adult surety in like sum. The matter was adjourned till January 31 for hearing